    "updated_at": "2014-09-05T05:01:53Z",
    "body": "Now I see that number casts are handled by `trans_imm_cast()` here\n- https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/blob/master/src/librustc/middle/trans/expr.rs#L1875\n\nBasically they are translated into [`LLVMBuildSExtOrBitCast`](http://llvm.org/docs/doxygen/html/group__LLVMCCoreInstructionBuilder.html) etc. which wrap [`llvm::CastInst`](http://llvm.org/docs/doxygen/html/classllvm_1_1CastInst.html)\n\nSeems like they are all implemented in the \"least surprising\" way for C programmers, but still, they should be rigorously defined/documented in the language reference manual because they are fundamental in a serious system programming.\n",
